reviews.review: Wasn't a fan of the direction of episodes 7-8.  Rise of Skywalker tries to tie up the Skywalker saga the best way they can.  This is probably the best they could have done all things considered.

(this review contains spoilers) 
Utterly lacking in what we were promised, for many fans this movie is devoid of the hope and satisfaction we were told it would have. The pacing is awful, any moment which could have held real emotional promise is rushed past without letting the audience sink into it. There are too many new elements and characters added in for shallow laughs or weak inspiration that they did not have time to fully explore. Sidestepping established characters storylines in the process of adding new, where was Rose Tico? She barely got any screentime at all, an injustice to a rich an interesting character.
The worst sin this movie commits in my opinion is that the Skywalker legacy is utterly decimated in every way imaginable and ultimately Palpatine wins with every Skywalker dead and his granddaughter surviving them. It turned all nine movies into the hopeless saga of a family ruined and tortured by a great evil to the bitter end with no hope of redemption or healing left. To make matters worse the death of the last Skywalker is blown over and never acknowledged in a rushed and soulless ending. There is no mourning, no honoring, no peace for the skywalker legacy. There is a awkward celebration in light of Ben's death moments before and a broken and lonely girl left exactly where she began, utterly alone in a barren desert.
This is the must see movie of the holidays and does not disappoint! Solid film, will probably still split hardcore fans feelings on the newest trilogy. Much better than The Last Jedi!
Best of the Sequel Trilogy. Hurt by only developing most of the new cast in this one.
The action and build up pretty good but For a franchise that lasted this long, it ended in a obvious manner, too predictable, they left too many things unanswered. The ending was very unsatisfying.

It was good seeing new and old faces in the continual struggle to live in free space.  Great special effects and story line that involved new problems in an old fight. Strange that some could breathe and be heard in open space with no mechanical assist but so goes the mystery of existing in a space void. Once again, the secret was to attack the biggest ship so there was redundancy. The right people died...the right people survived. The movie can be emotional for those who have been following from the beginnings. Well worth the price of the ticket to see the twists and turns many have hoped for.
The story brought everything together in a nice way. Beautiful scenes with Leia, great light saber fights and beautiful ending . Loved the movie .
